<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub147.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm1.showMessage?topicID=38397.topic">pub147.ezboard.com/fmonkl...8397.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
And now since I think its relevant I will repost my thoughts here. <br>
<br>
<br>
I'm so sick of my warrior right now its not even funny. Im sick of excuses from people and from SoE. We bitch about taunt, mitigation, useless AA's, we get the same story every time. No one wants an upgraded taunt for the warrior because then they say......<br>
<br>
&quot;It would make hunting trivial and do away with aggro management&quot;<br>
<br>
THATS SO MUCH BULL <br>
<br>
/eyetwitches <br>
<br>
Newsflash folks the only reason my warrior tanks any better then a pal/SK is because I have a fricken discipline. Yes for a few seconds you can notice a increase in my mitigation abilities. SK/pals have lower caps, it doesnt matter. It really doesn't, the equipment available out there truly does make up for their lower caps. <br>
<br>
They can pull aggro on a dime anytime they want, tank just as well as us in 90% of raid encounters and have a zillion options for fun. What do I have, someone tell me. Please let me know what I have. Wait ill tell you what I have<br>
<br>
A half assed taunt ability<br>
Crits that fire off at normal damage 80% of the time (which other classes now have)<br>
A defensive discipline that I Can use once every 12 weeks<br>
98% reliablility on Proc weapons for help with AGGRO<br>
A horribly painstaking epic for a half assed reward only good for the proc <br>
AA Melee skills that fire off at such low percentages that you may never see them for hours. But if or when they do they only increase DPS by a minute amount <br>
A hitpoint advantage that can be made up for by other means<br>
<br>
<br>
What do I bring to a group? Nothing, piss poor DPS, piss poor Aggro control, piss poor Damage mitigation. <br>
<br>
what do I have....<br>
<br>
So my fellow warriors, go on and keep preaching how we are fine. We aren't, we were made into a dull, useless class that is slowly taking its place on the bandwagon of classes to put down previously occupied by the ranger and the paly. You other classes shouldn't feel sorry for us, we let it happen to ourselves. Telling ourselves we are fine, finding other means to make up for our lack of abilities we should of always had and always been wonderful at. <br>
<br>
<br>
Windance Warwillow<br>
Pissed off warrior <br>
Brell Serilis<br>
The drunks of Tunare<br>
