<br>
Dobbanz, I agree that the measures SOE took were too extreme.  I agree that it's a good thing they fixed part of it.  I've said in a couple of places, gratz to the Monks.  However, what I don't particularly care for is the fairly predominate Monk opinion that I've seen that there was no cause for the change <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>at all</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.  I disagree.  I always have.  And I've not made that a secret.<br>
<br>
We have three tank classes in this game already all vying for the same slot in a group.  We do <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>not</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> under any circumstances need a fourth.  One of the very first posts about the un-nerf on MB I saw was someone remarking how they had tanked a PoV mob and done just fine.  This bugs the crap out of me.  I think Monks should take damage like a Ranger, to be honest.  And I've grouped with Monks in the past pre-nerf who completely disregarded aggro control, refusing to allow me to tank, because they felt they took the damage just as well as I did.  And they didn't seem to be far from wrong.<br>
<br>
I already hold aggro like crap.  My class is already the number three choice to tank in PoP.  The last thing I want is for the Monks to start dising us again too.<br>
<br>
I have misgivings about the roll back.  I'm not sure what the impact is going to be.  And while I wait and see what the story really is, I know that if a Monk can't find a group now he can go find some low blues someplace and probably solo.  While if I can't find a group, well I might as well just log and be done with it.<br>
